                <note/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>To Correspondents Once More</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"We have several times requested gentlemen who are discussing the merits of
                    candidates for office to curtail the length of their communications. . . . So
                    far our requests have not only been unheeded, but communications have actually
                    grown longer."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Spectator urges its correspondents again to limit their letters regarding
                    merits of candidates and claims that it will not print lengthy letters unless
                    they are at the paper office by Friday before publication.</summary>
                <note/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>The Position of Mr. Bates</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Spectator believes that Edward Bates will receive very little support in
                    the South for a Presidential nomination, as he has come down on the Republican
                    side of the slavery issue.</summary>
                <note/>
            </div>
